            <title>[CASSANDRA-19719] CEP-15: (Accord) When nodes are removed from a cluster, need to update topology tracking to avoid being blocked</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/CASSANDRA-19719</link>
                <project id="12310865" key="CASSANDRA">Apache Cassandra</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;When doing a host replacement or decom nodes will leave the cluster and won&apos;t ever come back, this can put accord&apos;s topology sync logic into a bad state as its going to wait forever for those nodes to acknowledge the epoch or parts of the ranges.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
